<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Capon" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Capon,</orth> castrated cock: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 4, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.154" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 8</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.502" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 502</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.502" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 502</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 100</bibl>. Used as a term of reproach: <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 1, 25</bibl> (perhaps == <emph>cap on;</emph> i. e. with a coxcomb). Quibbling, like the French <emph>poulet,</emph> for a love-letter: <cit><quote>Boyet, you can carve; break up this c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 56</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>